text: Loved it. Just a well shot action film that somewhat pays homage to the John Woo films of the 80's in Hong Kong cinema. The story is straight forward but has wonderful world building along the way that keeps the world John Wick inhabits fresh and expansive. The violence isn't put in the dark, it's upfront and gruesome. Great performances all around with Keanu still establishing his greatly appreciated comeback. Angry and brooding it's a middle finger to his typecast "surfer stoner airhead" roles that brought him fame. Can't wait for Chapter 3.

text: Violence, violence, ah glorious violence! What I didn't like - The infernal censorship. Kill woman, Good. Show naked woman, Bad. The plot, ridiculous! But it's to keep the action going (and it DOES!) What I liked - The action is going, going. But never gone.  If you just like shoot shoot blam slam kill kill. Oh and punching, kicking, and hitting people with cars, SEE THIS MOVIE. Mild gore. The movie specializes in breathtaking, almost nonstop, action of violent nature. I've seen it elsewhere, and it's probably the same here.       ***** SPOILER*****    I don't actually know if you all would call this a happy ending or not. But it sure does for the most part, fix everything that needs fixing! Especially your shameful need to see violence and more violence.  It's not "real" but it sure feels real while you're watching it.  That's some God damn yummy violence there! YUMMY But for you moralizers out there, once you shut it off, the violence stops, and you didn't so much as touch a soul.
